{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Multiple adapters could be fine-tuned, each targeting and using the same frozen NLP model for each fine-tuned adapter [34].Large Language Models (LLMs) demand substantial video random memory(VRAM) resources, making memory-efficient fine-tuning and continuous training techniques essential.",
    "Quantized LoRA (QLoRA) [18] addresses this challenge by enabling the training and adaptation of LLMs using quantized representations.",
    "This method involves converting the model's weights to a 4-bit format, effectively reducing memory footprint while preserving performance.",
    "During training, gradients are backpropagated through the quantized weights to update the model [57].",
    "QLoRA further enhances efficiency through double quantization, a technique that quantizes the quantization constants themselves, achieving additional memory savings of approximately 0.37 bits per parameter [18]."
  ],
